{
  "texts": [
    "Leiter et al. (2023) and Tounsi et al. (2023) also applied emotion classification models to examine the public reactions expressed in tweets.",
    "Studies that focused on specific areas like cybersecurity (Okey et al. 2023), healthcare (Praveen and Vajrobol 2023), or education (Li et al. 2023, Fütterer et al. 2023) examined tweets with relatively longer time spans, ranging from 2 to 4 months.",
    "For sentiment analysis, these studies either used the lexicon-and rule-based VADER model (Hutto and Gilbert 2014) or a pre-trained BERT model like Twitter-roBERTa (Barbieri et al. 2020), both of which we evaluated for performance in our study.",
    "To perform topic modeling, three of these studies used BERTopic (Praveen and Vajrobol 2023, Li et al. 2023, Fütterer et al. 2023), while Okey et al. (2023) used LDA.",
    "The studies mentioned above revealed either the overall or per-topic sentiments of the public toward ChatGPT in tweets."
  ]
}